caller_intent: Tracy is attempting to resolve an issue where Heather has not received an email she sent, which is critical for client-related matters.
resolution_steps: Tracy confirms with Heather whether she received an email.
Heather states she hasn't checked her email and later confirms she didn't see it.
Tracy suggests checking the spam folder and confirms she will resend the email.
Heather agrees to wait and check again.
knowledge_required: Understanding of email delivery issues and spam filtering
systems_referenced: Email client (implied through discussion of spam and resending emails)
summary: Tracy and Heather discuss a missing email related to a client. Tracy agrees to resend the email and check spam, while Heather will wait and verify receipt. The call appears to be a transferred extension conversation focused on resolving an email delivery issue.
